			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-452342">
									

<p>Unless I'm mistaken, "narm" is when something is meant to be taken seriously, but for some reason comes across as funny instead.</p>
<p>In this case, it's because the doctor in this relatively serious test has the same name as the one from one of the silliest test logs. Easy enough to change though.</p>
<p>On the subject of the SCP itself, I like the idea, the test log is perhaps a little more graphic than is necessary. I would consider a bit of [DATA EXPUNGED] in order here.</p>

